I truely appreciate your kind words, Ed!<br><br>
&quot;I feel okay about lamenting the severe hardships and horrors that you and others endured.. but don't like reliving my own sadness.. maybe I'm afraid of being weak.&quot;<br><br>
There are times that I remember the horrors, but don't recall the fears or other emotions. Then there are times when they are so close to me that I feel that I am back in those situations. These past few months since I had my brain surgery, I wake up each morning wondering if this was to be my last day on this earth. My writing has deteriated to the extent that I have a great difficulty expressing what I want to pass on. My reading skills suck so much that I have to sit on and re-read posts from others for a couple of days just so I can understand what they want me to understand. It could have been easier just to forget this site and stay hundled within my home. It would definately have been much easier not to go through therapy every weekday, including physical and mental rehab which wears me down. There are times when I am with others that I have a difficult time understanding what they are saying. There are times I feel like the stereotypical basket case, slouch in a chair, drooling in his own lap, making babbeling noises.<br><br>
It has been apparent that when things get serious, you start out with the joking. I accept that. But I have just laid out my everyday weaknesses for all to see. I don't feel anybody will make light with anything that I have written here. I cannot fathom anybody making light of those times that we speak of either, should you decide to write them down someday.
<p><code>-- docdel@maui.net  (Doc Del) </code><p>


